<paragraph id="050DF464FFEAFFE9D4EF34789662C91E" blockId="4.[869,1493,826,1011]" lastBlockId="5.[94,719,218,787]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEAFFE8D4EF34789002C95E" authorityName="Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1922" box="[907,1044,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Ameropterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEAFFE8D4EF34789002C95E" box="[907,1044,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ameropterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Neotropical genus with 21 species distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="7DA5B4F4FFEAFFE8D35734189094C97E" box="[1075,1154,858,883]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="7DA5B4F4FFEAFFE8D3DD34189131C97E" box="[1209,1319,858,883]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEAFFE8D259341891D9C97E" author="Penny, N. D." box="[1341,1487,858,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="176 - 186" refId="ref12390" refString="Penny, N. D. 2002. Family Ascalaphidae. In: Penny, N. D. A Guide to the Lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (4): 176 - 186; 293 - 299 (figs)." type="journal article" year="2002">Penny, 2002</bibRefCitation>
) (
<tableCitation id="4830C1DFFFEAFFE8D40F343897ADC99E" box="[875,955,890,915]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[170,220,218,243]" captionText="Table 1. List of the NewWorld split-eyed Ascalaphinae species." pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Table 1</tableCitation>
). The validity of the genus has been questioned since some of their diagnostic traits are overlapped with those of a Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEAFFE8D35E34F890F8C9DE" box="[1082,1262,954,979]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Ululodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEAFFE8D35E34F89080C9DE" box="[1082,1174,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ululodes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEAFFE8D39E34F89190C9DE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[1274,1414,954,979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="176 - 186" refId="ref12390" refString="Penny, N. D. 2002. Family Ascalaphidae. In: Penny, N. D. A Guide to the Lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (4): 176 - 186; 293 - 299 (figs)." type="journal article" year="2002">Penny, 2002</bibRefCitation>
). In the recent phylogenetic analysis of 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEAFFE8D3D9349891BEC9FE" author="Machado, R. J. P. &amp; Gillung, J. P. &amp; Winterton, S. L. &amp; Garzon-Orduna I. J. &amp; Lemmon A. R. &amp; Lemmon, E. M. &amp; Oswald, J. D." box="[1213,1448,986,1011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="418 - 450" refId="ref11518" refString="Machado, R. J. P.; Gillung, J. P.; Winterton, S. L.; Garzon-Orduna I. J.; Lemmon A. R.; Lemmon, E. M. &amp; Oswald, J. D. 2019. Owlflies are derived antlions: anchored phylogenomics supports a new phylogeny and classification of Myrmeleontidae (Neuroptera). Systematic Entomology, 44: 418 - 450, 2019." type="journal article" year="2019">
Machado 
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEAFFE8D24E3498914AC9FE" box="[1322,1372,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, the genus was recovered as paraphyletic.The group is distinguished by having wings elongated and narrow, sometimes with axillary angle of forewing moderately developed, and a distinct concavity on posterior wing margin plus an anal lobe on the hind wing. Antennal length is variable depending on the species, reaching laterally to level of forewing pterostigma or being longer than forewing.CuA (CuP 
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEBFFE9D66336F89555CBDE" box="[263,323,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D62236F895DDCBDE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[326,459,442,467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="176 - 186" refId="ref12390" refString="Penny, N. D. 2002. Family Ascalaphidae. In: Penny, N. D. A Guide to the Lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (4): 176 - 186; 293 - 299 (figs)." type="journal article" year="2002">Penny,2002</bibRefCitation>
)of hind wing is straight, whereas MA and MP are subparallel (
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D68A36989695CBFE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[494,643,474,499]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref12267" refString="Penny, N. D. 1981 a. Review of the generic level classification of the NewWorld Ascalaphidae (Neuroptera). Acta Amazonica, 11 (2): 391 - 406. http: // www. scielo. br / pdf / aa / v 11 n 2 / 1809 - 4392 - aa- 11 - 2 - 0391. pdf." type="journal article" year="1981">Penny, 1981a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D5EF369896D0CBFE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[651,710,474,499]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="176 - 186" refId="ref12390" refString="Penny, N. D. 2002. Family Ascalaphidae. In: Penny, N. D. A Guide to the Lacewings (Neuroptera) of Costa Rica. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 53 (4): 176 - 186; 293 - 299 (figs)." type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
). Male ectoproct is unmodified, lacking ventral clasper-like projections as in 
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEBFFE9D67A35589635C83E" authority="(Shetlar, 1977)" baseAuthorityName="Shetlar" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[286,547,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Ululodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEBFFE9D67A3558956CC83E" box="[286,378,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ululodes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D6E33558960AC83E" author="Shetlar, D. J." box="[391,540,538,563]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref12474" refString="Shetlar, D. J. 1977. The biosystematics of the Nearctic Ascalaphidae (Insecta: Neuropteroidea: Planipennia), with notes on biology and morphology. Ph. D. dissertation. Pennsylvania State University, University Park, Pennsylvania." type="book" year="1977">Shetlar, 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The genus has not been never reported in 
<collectingCountry id="7DA5B4F4FFEBFFE9D6C43578961BC85E" box="[416,525,570,595]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, but most of the species are known from neighboring countries. Species identification can be made with certain reliability following the works of 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D67535D895E1C8BE" author="Van der Weele, H. W." box="[273,503,666,691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref12678" refString="Van der Weele, H. W. 1909. Ascalaphiden. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, Catalogue Systematique et Descriptif, 8: 1 - 326." type="journal article" year="1909">Van der Weele (1909)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D54F35D896DDC8BE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[555,715,666,691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="605 - 651" refId="ref12333" refString="Penny, N. D. 1981 b. Neuroptera of the Amazon Basin. Part 3. Ascalaphidae. Acta Amazonica, 11: 605 - 651. https: // acta. inpa. gov. br / fasciculos / 11 - 3 / PDF / v 11 n 3 a 20. pdf." type="journal article" year="1981">Penny (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D73A35F89504C8DE" author="Heckman, C. W." box="[94,274,698,723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref11338" refString="Heckman, C. W. 2017. Neuroptera (including Megaloptera). Encyclopedia of South American aquatic insects. Illustrated keys to the known families, genera, and species in South America. Switzerland, Springer. i-xvi, 621 p." type="book" year="2017">Heckman (2017)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a taxonomic key based on the works of 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D7A135989549C8FE" author="Penny, N. D." box="[197,351,730,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref12267" refString="Penny, N. D. 1981 a. Review of the generic level classification of the NewWorld Ascalaphidae (Neuroptera). Acta Amazonica, 11 (2): 391 - 406. http: // www. scielo. br / pdf / aa / v 11 n 2 / 1809 - 4392 - aa- 11 - 2 - 0391. pdf." type="journal article" year="1981">Penny (1981a</bibRefCitation>
, b, 2002) and on the original descriptions and keys of 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D63535B895F0C91E" author="Navas, L." box="[337,486,762,787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="45 - 143" refId="ref11888" refString="Navas, L. 1912 a. Sinopsis de los Ascalafidos (Ins. Neur.). Arxius de l'Institut de Ciencies, Institut d'Estudis Catalans, SecciO de Ciencies, 1: 45 - 143." type="journal article" year="1912">Navás (1912a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D68A35B89631C91E" author="Navas, L." box="[494,551,762,787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="287 - 305" refId="ref11981" refString="Navas, L. 1919. Algunos insectos Neuropteros de la Republica Argentina. Serie tercera [III]. Revista de la Real Academia de Ciencias Exactas Fisicas y Naturales de Madrid, 17: 287 - 305." type="journal article" year="1919">1919</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEBFFE9D55435B8967CC91E" author="Navas, L." box="[560,618,762,787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="53 - 66" refId="ref12021" refString="Navas, L. 1932. Insectos Suramericanos. Quinta Serie. Revista de la Real Academia de Ciencias Exactas, Fisicas y Naturales de Madrid, 29 (14): 53 - 66." type="journal article" year="1932">1932</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
